 a strong visual art student. She shows a high level of thought and attention to detail in her work, resulting in very successful pieces of art.  I hope she continues to use her creativity in the future.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\nMs. Brianna Balboni'),(3321,1163,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 08:33:02','2011-12-15 08:33:02','Sem1','Uakuu is a curious student who often asks questions. He is generally interested in stretching his understanding of the cosmos.'),(3322,3045,2,1,'2011-12-15 08:34:18','2011-12-15 08:34:18','Sem1',''),(3323,1757,NULL,1,'2011-12-15 08:34:50','2011-12-15 08:34:50','Sem1','William has done an excellent job of understanding the conceptually difficult elements of the course. He is a curious student who asks questions to further his own understanding and has been engaged in all parts of the course.'),(3324,191,NULL,1,'2011-12-15 08:35:39','2011-12-16 09:29:22','Sem1','Nkotseng continues to be a strong visual art student who applies skills in a variety of assignments.  She shows strong attention to detail in her work.  Nkotseng struggled to retain some art history information we learned this semester, and should work on making those connections stronger in the future.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\nMs. Brianna Balboni '),(3325,1747,NULL,1,'2011-12-15 08:36:57','2011-12-15 08:36:57','Sem1','William has a good tone on his tenor saxophone.  He is a hard worker and contributes positively to the class at all times.  To excel, William is encouraged to heed to the articulation and dynamic markings on his instrument and work on his rhythm reading skills.  Overall, William has been an asset to the middle school band! '),(3326,1344,NULL,1,'2011-12-15 08:44:33','2011-12-15 08:44:33','Sem1','Yema continues to excel at playing the clarinet.  To further improve, Yema can blow more air into her clarinet to differentiate the spectrum of dynamics she can play!  Overall, Yema is doing well and should keep up the great work. '),(3327,3167,5,4,'2011-12-15 08:45:28','2011-12-15 08:45:28','Sem1',''),(3328,3082,3,1,'2011-12-15 08:46:01','2011-12-15 08:46:01','Sem1',''),(3329,3070,5,2,'2011-12-15 08:46:11','2012-01-10 07:05:36','Sem1',''),(3330,2933,5,4,'2011-12-15 08:46:41','2011-12-15 08:46:41','Sem1',''),(3331,3238,5,1,'2011-12-15 08:46:55','2011-12-15 08:47:14','Sem1',''),(3332,1083,NULL,1,'2011-12-15 08:57:09','2011-12-15 08:57:09','Sem1','Yohanna continues to improve in her clarinet playing.  She has excellent knowledge of music terminology and their applications.  To further improve, she would benefit from blowing more air into the clarinet so that she can exercise the spectrum of dynamics to the fullest.  Yohanna, keep up the excellent work! '),(3333,3753,NULL,5,'2011-12-15 09:00:34','2011-12-15 09:00:34','Sem1','Kurbell started off the quarter well - he came in for help, was able to play parts of a scale and had good tone quality on his trombone.  However, he has done little practice when offered after school time slots and given specific homework.  Easily, Kurbell could be a fantastic trombone player.  However, his lack of practice has not contributed positively to his playing.  Kurbell is always welcome to come in for help and practice with friends.  He, however, needs to initiate these rehearsals and ask for help. '),(3334,2976,4,2,'2011-12-15 09:05:16','2011-12-15 09:05:16','Sem1',''),(3335,3091,2,1,'2011-12-15 09:05:52','2011-12-15 09:05:52','Sem1',''),(3336,2836,3,1,'2011-12-15 09:06:19','2011-12-15 09:06:43','Sem1',''),(3337,3101,3,2,'2011-12-15 09:07:55','2011-12-15 09:07:55','Sem1',''),(3338,3249,2,1,'2011-12-15 09:08:05','2011-12-15 09:08:05','Sem1',''),(3339,3129,2,1,'2011-12-15 09:08:40','2011-12-15 09:08:40','Sem1',''),(3340,3146,3,1,'2011-12-15 09:09:01','2011-12-15 09:09:01','Sem1',''),(3341,2967,2,1,'2011-12-15 09:09:32','2011-12-15 09:09:32','Sem1',''),(3342,3162,4,1,'2011-12-15 09:10:03','2011-12-15 09:10:03','Sem1',''),(3343,2822,2,1,'2011-12-15 09:10:36','2011-12-15 09:10:36','Sem1',''),(3344,562,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 09:39:59','2011-12-16 10:26:52','Sem1','Abigail has done very well on many of the science benchmarks.  It seems that she has forgotten a few of the skills we worked on mostly during the first quarter and so we just need to review and re-fresh these with her.  Other than that, I am very please with Abigail\'s progress.  Keep working hard!\r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3345,595,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 09:44:17','2011-12-16 10:36:22','Sem1','Kayleigh has shown a lot of strength and determination this quarter.  She has been focused on improving her science skills and her hard work has paid off.  Her accurate measurement skills in particular are much better.  An important aspect of a good scientist.  We will continue to work on experimental design and identifying variables in the 3rd quarter.  Keep working hard Kayleigh.\r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3346,334,NULL,4,'2011-12-15 09:46:32','2011-12-16 10:38:26','Sem1','Dear Tommy,  \r\nI really enjoyed my short half-year with you.  You are a good scientist with lots of logic and inquisitiveness (ask your mom).  Remember to stay on top of your studies and assignments, read questions carefully, and you will do great! \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3347,679,NULL,4,'2011-12-15 09:49:04','2011-12-16 10:36:54','Sem1','Wilson is definitely improving in his science skills.  We practiced using the triple beam balance and it helped!   There are still areas which need to be worked on and improved.  I know Wilson is a very capable student.   if he continues to work hard on his assignments at home and we continue our after school sessions, I think much progress can be made. \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3348,64,NULL,4,'2011-12-15 09:54:27','2011-12-16 10:34:50','Sem1','Hafeleni has improved her science work habits a lot.  Coming after school one day a week along with better focus in class (and at home) has helped her improve in many benchmarks.  There are just a few areas that still need attention.  I would like to continue this once a week after school session for Semester 2.  Keep working hard, Hafeleni.  \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3349,51,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 09:55:49','2011-12-16 10:30:13','Sem1','Great work Aida.  Your understanding of the buoyancy labs is excellent!  I would like to see you take on an independent study or experiment in the 3rd quarter to explore an aspect of science that you might like and to further your science skills. Keep working hard. \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3350,239,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 10:02:30','2011-12-16 10:35:34','Sem1','Hanna, I appreciate your enthusiasm and inquisitive nature in science class.  You have a solid  understanding of the science skills and comments, though you need to be careful with the details.  Keep\r\nup the good work and think about doing an independent study or experiment in the 3rd quarter to explore an aspect of science that you might like.\r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3351,275,NULL,4,'2011-12-15 10:09:01','2011-12-16 10:45:05','Sem1','Lara has improved a great deal in both her science skills and knowledge.  She needs to be more careful with details, for example, measuring to the nearest tenth and remembering all the parts of a graph.  Lara did a great job with the soil and scarification labs.  Keep up the good work. \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3352,118,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 10:10:41','2011-12-16 10:42:51','Sem1','Nikita works hard, works fast and works focused.  She does not take time to ponder but gets on with business and gets it done.  She has a great understanding of basic science theory and how to conduct experiments.  She can read instructions.  I hope Nikita will consider doing an independent study or experiment in the 3rd quarter to explore an aspect of science that she might like.  Keep up the good work.  \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3353,135,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 10:13:07','2011-12-16 10:43:58','Sem1','Maria is a quiet and steady worker in class.  She definitely participates in class discussions but when it comes to labs she is focused and on task.  She shows a very solid understand of the benchmarks for Semester 1.  Maria did a great job with understanding our buoyancy labs and answered the \'exceeds the standard\' questions very well.  I hope Maria will consider doing an independent study or experiment in the 3rd quarter to explore an aspect of science that she might like.  Keep working hard. \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3354,76,NULL,4,'2011-12-15 10:14:59','2011-12-16 10:43:25','Sem1','Martin has a much improved attitude as well as performance during this past quarter.  I am hoping that he sees that one influences the other.  He has shown very solid laboratory skills as well as understanding of our buoyancy and soil experiments. We shall continue to work on density experiments in the third quarter, so I am not worried about that benchmark.  He has made excellent contributions to class discussions and I hope he continues to do that in Semester 2.  \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3355,497,NULL,5,'2011-12-15 10:18:12','2011-12-16 10:41:15','Sem1','Ntsika is able to do very good work when focused.  He needs to improve his self-discipline to have that focus and be willing to put in the work it takes to complete assignments.  I highly recommend that he works in my classroom one afternoon a week (not Wednesdays) to keep him up to date on assignments.  He has achieved well on many benchmarks but needs to still improve in some basic ones. \r\nSincerely,  Ms. Ashby'),(3356,442,NULL,1,'2011-12-15 10:20:12','2012-01-23 07:55:47','Sem1','Ruhama has worked very hard this semester and achieved very well on all her learning benchmarks for science.  In particular, she has exceeded the standard in her measurement skills (and relating them to buoyancy) as well as her ability to define variables in an experiment.  Excellent work.  Keep it up for the next semester.\r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3357,452,NULL,1,'2011-12-15 10:24:11','2011-12-16 10:42:12','Sem1','Nomonde has continued to excel in her studies of science.  She has excellent laboratory skills as well as analyzing skills.  She exceeded the standard in her understanding of the buoyancy concepts we have been studying.  I hope she continues her plans to do an independent study/ experiment on seeds.  Keep up the good work.  \r\nMs. Ashby'),(3358,90,NULL,1,'2011-12-15 10:39:39','2011-12-16 10:37:40','Sem1','Wedu is a steady, hard worker.  She is very disciplined about her work inside and outside of class.  I appreciate this hard work ethic and believe that she achieves so well directly because of it!   I look forward to seeing how her independent study/experiment turns out during the next semester.  Keep up the good work.\r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3359,368,NULL,4,'2011-12-15 10:42:57','2011-12-16 10:39:18','Sem1','Sidney has done fine in all of the benchmarks except for graphing and interpreting graphs.  I am sure this would only take a short review to \'remind\' him of how to do this.  He has a good understanding of experiments and how the variables play a part in them.  He has difficulty getting assignments in on time, participating in class discussions and working with non-friend lab partners.  I would appreciate a little more focus and intentness in class.  I think this would benefit Sidney in many ways.  \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3360,538,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 10:47:55','2011-12-16 09:26:07','Sem1','In the second quarter, Ms. Ashby was a bit lazy and did not translate any tests or other documents for Ana Sofia.  This did not seem to matter to her!  She has done an outstanding job in science in English!   \r\nI am impressed with her ability to adapt and learn so quickly!  Great job.  I appreciate your hard work and will have to figure out a way to challenge you in quarter 3!  \r\nSincerely,  Ms. Ashby'),(3361,669,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 10:49:59','2011-12-16 09:26:46','Sem1','If there was a prize for \'most improved\',  Annmarie would get it for her work in science.  She has really improved in her understanding of concepts and her lab skills, as well as her ability to organize herself.  I am very impressed and appreciate all her hard work.  I think the one day a week after school sessions are working very well and would like to continue this in the third quarter.  Keep up the great work Annmarie.  Sincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3362,44,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 10:51:40','2011-12-16 09:27:32','Sem1','Briana is doing a great job.  She has a solid understanding of all the semester 1 benchmarks.  On the metric skills test 2, she answered the exceed the standard questions for buoyancy and identifying variables well enough to bump her up her grade.   I would like to see Briana take on an independent study or experiment in the 3rd quarter to explore an aspect of science that she might like and to develop her experiment design skills as well. Keep up the good work! \r\nSincerely,  Ms. Ashby '),(3363,2948,17,1,'2011-12-15 11:12:16','2011-12-15 11:12:16','Sem1',''),(3364,1,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 11:13:40','2011-12-16 10:04:10','Sem1','Abale is doing a great job in science and is very competent in all the benchmarks except perhaps density, which we will continue to work on in Quarter 3 anyway.  She must be careful to always record to the accuracy that is allowed by the instrument (to the near tenth in our equipment).  She is a good lab partner and participates often in class discussions.  Keep working hard Abale!\r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3365,171,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 11:15:51','2011-12-16 10:05:45','Sem1','Abigail, or Abi -B as I call her,  works very hard both in class and out.  She has done well to achieve and improve on a lot of her science skills.  We will continue to work on the design of experiments and therefore review variables and how to define and identify them in a lab.  I appreciate Abigail\'s serious and purposeful approach to the labs we do in class. Keep up the good work. \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby'),(3366,3293,17,1,'2011-12-15 11:16:43','2011-12-15 11:16:43','Sem1',''),(3367,3242,17,1,'2011-12-15 11:17:01','2011-12-15 11:17:01','Sem1',''),(3368,227,NULL,4,'2011-12-15 11:17:31','2011-12-16 10:06:32','Sem1','Ahmed has some very good contributions to some of our class discussions.  I appreciate his ideas and insights but also feel he needs to develop some discipline in how he approaches his work.  This self-discipline would include keeping himself focused during lab or review times, asking questions if he doesn\'t understand, and completing assignments to the full extent.  Ahmed is capable of all these things, he just has to decide that he will do it.  I feel our after school session are helpful and we should continue in quarter 3.  \r\nSincerely, Ms. Ashby\r\n'),(3369,2982,17,1,'2011-12-15 11:17:43','2011-12-15 11:17:43','Sem1',''),(3370,1406,NULL,4,'2011-12-15 11:18:06','2011-12-16 06:49:37','Sem1','Adam:\r\n-does well on assessments\r\n-rarely comes to class unprepared \r\n-needs to ask more questions in class when confused\r\n-needs to take more responsibility for his learning\r\n\r\nNice job this semester!'),(3371,1215,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 11:18:45','2011-12-16 06:50:21','Sem1','Ashley:\r\n-has begun to participate more in class\r\n-is always on task\r\n-often forgets her book\r\n\r\nNice job this semester!'),(3372,262,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 11:19:10','2011-12-16 10:07:06','Sem1','David has done very well on all the semester 1 benchmarks.  He has a good approach to the science labs in class and is very purposeful in his actions.  I would like to see David take on an independent study or experiment in the 3rd quarter to explore an aspect of science that he might like and to develop his experiment design skills as well. Keep working hard. \r\nSincerely,  Ms. Ashby '),(3373,1287,NULL,2,'2011-12-15 11:19:10','2011-12-16 06:51:35','Sem1','Batch:\r\n-does very well with concepts as shown on assessments\r\n-sometimes comes to class with incomplete homework\r\n-is very distracting to others in class\r\n\r\nNice job this semester!'),(3374,3230,17,1,'2011-12-15 11:19:13','2011-12-15 11:19:13','Sem1',''),(3375,22