 Sophi has been performing at a 4 level on all of her assignments. Unfortunately, Sophi is also very disorganized and however well meaning, her ability to show her knowledge suffers as a consequence. For example, more than once she has insisted that she has done the homework, but is unable to find the file on her laptop. This means that both she and I have to spend time and energy getting the work in late. My suggestions to her are as follows:\r\n1. For her computer: Sophi should create more specific file names for each fileâ€”History, History 1 and History 2â€”give no indication of what is in the files. One easy thing to do for in-class work is add the date to the file name. This way she can see when the file was first created, not when it was last saved.\r\n2. For her work: Sophi should pack her school bag before going to sleep each night and make time to explain what she has completed for homework for the next day.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions please contact me,\r\n\r\nBrian Greenough\r\nBrian.Greenough@icsaddis.edu.et \r\n0913-026-646\r\n','2011-11-18 06:53:32','2011-11-18 12:31:17'),(224,1134,5,NULL,'Q2','Unacceptable','Occasionally','Unacceptable','Always','Alex continues to be off-task most of the time in class.  This is very clear when reading her answers to summative assessment questions - she is usually completely off target.  She has shown no effort in improving this despite many conversations and warnings.  \r\n\r\nThere is no way that Alex can be successful in class with her current attitude and lack of focus.  She seems to struggle with reading comprehension and her lack of effort only increases her difficulties.  \r\n\r\nI have talked with Alex many times but with no noticeable improvement in her behavior.    ','2011-11-18 06:54:03','2011-11-18 06:54:03'),(225,2032,16,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Usually','Unacceptable','Always','It is hard for me to give Zoe a grade in History because she has turned in very little work. Multiple times since October she has not brought her laptop to class and thus cannot turn in the work in that is claims on the laptop. When she does bring the laptop to class, Zoe has a hard time finding the work that she has done. If she does not want to use the laptop or bring it to school, then she needs to start doing her work by hand so that she has a chance of demonstrating her knowledge. Her missing assignments are as follows: Timeline of the French Revolution, Notes from Chapter 6 Section 4 and 5, a short essay on the impacts of the French Revolution on different social groups, Two Column Notes on Napoleon\'s reforms in France and a short essay on Napoleon\'s reforms in France. From this, it is not clear if she has done any work outside of class for the past two weeks.  \r\n\r\nIt would be a good thing for Zoe that she leave ICS at the semester with marks that reflect her best effort. Can you please ask her to finish these assignments and to turn them in? I will follow up as well and start to schedule time with her at lunch and after school for her to work on these assignments. \r\n\r\nIf you have any questions please contact me,\r\n\r\nBrian Greenough\r\nBrian.Greenough@icsaddis.edu.et \r\n0913-026-646','2011-11-18 06:57:55','2011-11-18 12:33:36'),(226,102,5,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Usually','Occasionally','Usually','Abdurrahim is making progress towards meeting the academic standards so far this quarter. However, he struggles with focus while writing independently. I feel he would benefit greatly if I could spend more time with him when there are fewer students in the classroom. I recommend that Abdurrahim meet with me on Monday or Tuesday weekly to focus on his writing until the winter break.','2011-11-18 07:04:28','2011-11-18 07:05:29'),(227,73,5,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Usually','Usually','Always','Martin is making progress towards meeting the standard so far this quarter but requires further assistance to meet the standards by the end of the quarter. Your child will need to demonstrate an improved understanding in the following areas to meet the standards by the end of the quarter:\r\n\r\n* Cite textual evidence to support analysis of what a text says explicitly as well as inferences drawn from the text.\r\n\r\n* Provide a summary of a text distinct from personal opinions or judgments.\r\n\r\n* Effectively discuss a text (one-on-one, in groups, and teacher- led) building on othersâ€™ ideas and expressing their own clearly.\r\n\r\n* Use narrative techniques, such as dialogue, pacing, and description, to develop experiences, events, and/or characters in his/her writing.\r\n\r\n*Use precise words and phrases, relevant descriptive details, and sensory language to convey experiences and events in his/her writing.\r\n\r\nI recommend that Martin work with an adult at least two times a week to better understand the above targets. I am available Monday and Tuesday after school to provide extra assistance and practice resources/ideas for your child. Rarely will these be one-on-one tutoring sessions since I will be working with multiple students. In addition, your child would greatly benefit from assistance from yourself or a tutor to properly prepare for upcoming assessments.','2011-11-18 07:09:31','2011-11-18 07:09:31'),(228,2889,4,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Always','Occasionally','Always','Since the meeting that Wubedel had with Ms. Halsey after the parent-teacher conferences, Wubedel has improved her participation and effort in class. She is more willing to talk about what she has learned and has tried to show her work. However, Wubedel still does not complete all of her homework, even when it is a modified or shortened reading. Also, when Wubedel is instructed to be working independently in class on modified assignments she will stop working and sit quietly until I notice her not working. She must stop giving up and not asking for help because this wastes a huge amount of her time. Wubedel will not improve her ability to read or write if she does not put consistent and sustained effort into the process. She also needs to show some attempt to complete the assignments that I give her, even if she is not able to finish. I cannot help her if I have no work of hers to base my feedback on.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions please contact me,\r\n\r\nBrian Greenough\r\nBrian.Greenough@icsaddis.edu.et \r\n0913-026-646','2011-11-18 07:27:36','2011-11-18 12:30:30'),(229,3117,5,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Always','Occasionally','Always','Khanya continues to work at the 3 to 4 range in IB History. She completes most of her assignments on on time, but does not ask questions when she does not understand. Her note taking can be incomplete and she does not always take notes during class. Khanya\'s essay writing will benefit from this quarter\'s focus on analysis. Unfortunately, Khanya was absent when we wrote our most recent essay on November 10th. She still needs to make this essay up in order to receive credit. \r\n\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions please contact me,\r\n\r\nBrian Greenough\r\nBrian.Greenough@icsaddis.edu.et \r\n0913-026-646','2011-11-18 07:37:14','2011-11-18 07:37:14'),(230,3299,5,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Usually','Always','After a rough start Ngatuuane had improved both in his effort and academics in my class. He now comes to class on time and makes a point to greet me. He has also been doing most of his homework on time and mostly complete. His writing will hopefully improve this quarter as we talk about how to create arguments that support thesis statements. His current work is very close to a 4 and if he keeps up the good effort, he should have a 4 by the semester. \r\n\r\nIf you have any questions please contact me,\r\n\r\nBrian Greenough\r\nBrian.Greenough@icsaddis.edu.et \r\n0913-026-646 ','2011-11-18 07:43:55','2011-11-18 12:41:39'),(231,3664,4,NULL,'Q2','Always','Always','Always','Always','Manisha continues to be a model student as she is always attentive and appears to be working hard. Unfortunately, this does not always translate into good performance on her assessments. It is possible that her grade can slip to a 3 by the end of the semester, especially if she has a bad essay or two. Manisha\'s essays suffer because she frequently confuses facts when doing the timed writings in class and will come to conclusions that do not make sense. I suggest that Manisha make flash cards of the essential vocabulary for each unit and spend 15 minutes a day going through the flash cards. This might help her to better remember her facts. The flash cards can be simple--term on the front and a quick definition on the back. \r\n\r\nIf you have any questions please contact me,\r\n\r\nBrian Greenough\r\nBrian.Greenough@icsaddis.edu.et \r\n0913-026-646','2011-11-18 08:01:51','2011-11-18 12:29:00'),(232,1138,5,NULL,'Q2','Unacceptable','Occasionally','Occasionally','Always','Alex shows the same lack of focus and effort in health as in science.  \r\n\r\n','2011-11-18 09:58:36','2011-11-18 09:58:36'),(233,1229,5,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Usually','Always','Jessica is reading at 8th grade level and clearly understanding a variety of texts both in class and for her independent reading standard.  She is also developing her participation in group discussions and gave a very confident, short oral book presentation in front of the whole group last week.  Her writing skills are approaching 8th grade level, and she needs to work on the following areas to develop this standard:  (1) structure and organization e.g. a clear introduction, body and conclusion to each piece of work (2) use of specific examples / evidence e.g. in response to literature and specific details / description e.g. in memoir narrative.  We also need to build Jessica\'s stamina in writing so she is able to write more in the time given.  I strongly recommend Study Hall (available Monday, Thursdays and Fridays from 3.30-4.30 in room 70 and Wednesdays 2.30-3.30 in the Library) once or twice per week to help with these skills.     ','2011-11-21 06:05:36','2011-11-21 06:05:36'),(234,1227,5,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Usually','Always','Jessica is very close to a 4 / meets standard in World Cultures at this point in the quarter, and I am confident she will meet standard in the near future.  She participates well in class activities, and easily answers questions which are teacher directed.  She needs to work on the following to help her reach the process standard of gathering and organizing information:  (1) Taking clear notes which include both main ideas and supporting details. (2) Making sure she brings all her notes and materials to each class so she has them readily available to prepare for tests / quizzes and so she can add to them during class discussions and presentations of new information.   I strongly recommend Study hall once or twice per week to review what we are doing in class (study hall in room 70 is available Mondays, Thursdays and Fridays from 3.30-4.30). ','2011-11-21 06:30:40','2011-11-21 06:30:40'),(235,1206,4,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Usually','Occasionally','Always','Although Calvin is meeting standard in World Cultures this quarter,I am issuing an interim report as I am concerned about some of his study habits - particularly his note taking skills in class and completing homework to the best of his abilities (including test preparation).\r\n\r\nThe process standard of gathering and organizing information is not always being met on formative assessments, as evidenced by weak note taking skills in class during reading, discussion and viewing activities.  In order to develop this standard, Calvin needs to (1) focus fully on the reading / discussion / viewing activity so he is able to record key points of information and supporting details (2) complete homework using full effort so that he has both test preparation notes and notes on short reading assignments ready for class discussions and quizzes.     \r\n\r\nCalvin may also benefit from attending Study hall once or twice per week to review work and complete short homeworks which are given occasionally in World Cultures.  Study hall in room 70 is available Mondays, Thursdays and Fridays from 3.30-4.30pm.              ','2011-11-21 06:46:24','2011-11-21 06:46:24'),(236,1726,4,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Occasionally','Always','Although DJ is meeting standard in World Cultures this quarter I am issuing an interim report as I am concerned about a number of his study habits - specifically effective note-taking in class and completing homework to the best of his abilities.\r\n\r\nHe participates well in class discussion activities but needs to focus more on the process standard of gathering and organizing information effectively.  If he does the following, I am confident he will continue to meet standard:  (1) focus fully on class reading, viewing and discussion activities so can record key ideas and supporting details in his notes and graphic organizers (2)complete homework such as short reading assignments and test review notes so he is able to fully participate in class and succeed on tests.  I strongly recommend Study Hall once or twice per week to develop these important study skills.  In Room 70, Study hall is available Mondays, Thursdays and Fridays from 3.30-4.30pm and Wednesdays from 2.30-3.30 in the Library.       ','2011-11-21 06:53:40','2011-11-21 06:53:40'),(237,1634,5,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Usually','Occasionally','Always','Jon participates well in full group discussions in World Cultures but is not yet meeting standard on this quarter\'s process skills of gathering, organizing and expressing information in multiple formats.  He needs to do the following to achieve standard in these areas:  (1) Focus fully on class reading, viewing and small group discussion activities so that he is able to record key ideas and supporting details effectively  (2)  Complete homework to the best of his abilities (including test preparation and short reading assignments).  He may benefit from Study hall to help develop these study habits.  In room 70, study hall is available Mondays, Thursdays and Fridays from 3.30-4.30pm and on Wednesdays from 2.30-3.30pm in the Library. ','2011-11-21 07:00:29','2011-11-21 07:00:29'),(238,284,10,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Occasionally','Always','\r\n Lara should put some more effort on her homework','2011-11-21 07:06:50','2011-11-21 07:06:50'),(239,1015,1,NULL,'Q2','Always','Always','Always','Always','','2011-11-21 07:07:33','2011-11-21 07:07:33'),(240,1043,1,NULL,'Q2','Always','Always','Always','Always','','2011-11-21 07:08:03','2011-11-21 07:08:03'),(241,1797,4,NULL,'Q2','Always','Always','Usually','Always','Stephen is doing very well in English Language Arts this quarter and participates well in all class activities.  He reads at 8th grade level and has a strong command of vocabulary.  \r\n\r\nI am issuing an interim report as his writing is not yet meeting standard.  I am confident if he does the following he will meet standard in the near future:  (1) develop his stamina in writing by writing every single day - e.g. in his reading notebook and in his writing notebook.  (2) develop his use of specific supporting details and examples e.g. in his response to literature and memoir narrative.\r\n\r\nStephen may also benefit from attending Study hall once or twice per week to have extra time to write.  Study hall is available in Room 70 Mondays, Thursdays and Fridays from 3.30-4.30pm and Wednesdays 2.30-3.30pm in the Library.   ','2011-11-21 07:09:21','2011-11-21 07:09:21'),(242,1049,10,NULL,'Q2','Always','Usually','Occasionally','Always','\r\nElliott should put more effort on his homework','2011-11-21 07:09:39','2011-11-21 07:09:39'),(243,1071,3,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Occasionally','Occasionally','Always','\r\n Benjamin has a good command of Spanish, but he should focus more on the activities of the class and on his homework','2011-11-21 07:12:09','2011-11-21 07:12:09'),(244,1202,10,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Usually','Occasionally','Always','\r\nCalvin has a good command of Spanish, but he should focus more on the activities of the class and on his homework','2011-11-21 07:13:28','2011-11-21 07:13:28'),(245,1724,11,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Usually','Occasionally','Always','\r\nDavid should put more effort on his work in class and on his homework','2011-11-21 07:14:44','2011-11-21 07:14:44'),(246,1758,1,NULL,'Q2','Always','Always','Always','Always','','2011-11-21 07:15:09','2011-11-21 07:15:09'),(247,2890,5,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Usually','Occasionally','Usually','Wubedel needs to push herself to participate in class daily.  This can help her develop her critical understanding and help her to practice  fully explaining her ideas.  This is especially important because at the moment she has shown low levels of understanding of what is required in her writing assignments.  ','2011-11-21 17:18:46','2011-11-22 06:44:16'),(248,3297,6,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Usually','Unacceptable','Usually','Nick has participated very well in class verbally.  However, he rarely does his homework, and he did not take his major written assessment seriously.  He has shown promise in the spoken areas of the course; he must now also deliver in the written portion.  ','2011-11-21 17:21:13','2011-11-21 17:21:13'),(249,3229,6,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Occasionally','Occasionally','Always','Mikeal needs to show renewed focus on deadlines and completion of homework.  It is only through doing assignments in the required way that he can develop the critical thinking skills necessary for success in this course.  He should additionally try to participate in whole class discussions at least once per meeting.\r\n\r\nHe has three weeks to pull his grade up to a passing grade of \'3\' for the semester, so immediate improvement is essential. ','2011-11-21 17:26:52','2011-11-22 06:42:41'),(250,3024,5,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Usually','Usually','Always','Mikko has recently shown better effort on his homework in terms of depth and length.  However, he must further develop his understanding of what is required of analytical assignments -- he has correctly identified and used key terms in texts, but has not discussed them depth, nor completely applied them in the proper context.  He should make an appointment to meet with me if he feels that any of the requirements of an assignment are unclear.','2011-11-21 17:30:50','2011-11-22 06:43:25'),(251,2816,5,NULL,'Q2','Always','Always','Occasionally','Usually','Niamh has shown an excellent attitude and enthusiastic participation in class since the parent-teacher conference.  Unfortunately, she did fall short of expectations on her major written assignment - while she did hand in a draft ahead of our revised schedule and met with me to go over it, she did not make a single revision that we discussed before handing it in as a \'final\' piece via email, 3 days past the day we agreed upon -- which was before she fell ill.  We need consistency and commitment to the parts of the course that Niamh is finding difficult as well as to the ones that come more naturally to her, in order to help her advance academically.','2011-11-21 17:40:27','2011-11-22 06:44:59'),(252,2284,3,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Usually','Occasionally','Usually','Natty fulfilled the formal requirements for his persuasive writing piece that resulted in his INC grade, and hopefully now has a better idea how to approach future pieces.  He picked a topic he had a lot of interest in and did well with it, but can still push himself further in specific exemplification and analysis.  He also needs to be more consistent in effort on homework and proper usage of his laptop.  ','2011-11-22 09:03:12','2011-11-22 09:03:12'),(253,2343,4,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Usually','Usually','Deborah has shown good effort in both group and class discussion.  She still needs to work on her organization and attention to detail in assignments, which was a big reason she ended quarter 1 with an INC grade.  However, she remedied the issues she had with her persuasive piece, which turned out to be the best example of writing that I\'ve seen from her to date. ','2011-11-22 09:07:20','2011-11-22 12:10:51'),(254,2394,4,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Occasionally','Usually','Diji has done a great job in class discussion so far this year.  He needs to find how to harness the focus and analysis he shows daily in this regard and translate it into his writing, which is often too short, or without necessary exemplification or analysis.  Also basic attention to detail such a spell check / grammar check / format check is a must for graded assignments.','2011-11-22 09:11:42','2011-11-22 09:11:42'),(255,2475,4,NULL,'Q2','Occasionally','Usually','Unacceptable','Usually','Christian still has not been prepared for class the way he needs to be, particularly with written assignments, which are generally far too brief or nonexistent.  He finally sorted out the formatting issues with his persuasive piece which led to his INC grade for quarter 1, but he did not give it the necessary attention in regards to research, exemplification, and analysis, and thus to date has achieved a grade far below his capabilities.','2011-11-22 09:14:46','2011-11-22 09:14:46'),(256,2312,4,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Occasionally','Always','Thabang has shown better engagement in class activities this year and lately has made more attempts at participation in whole-class discussion; I would like to see these trends continue to develop positively.  However, he is still having problems with completing assignments on time and having all materials he needs for every class.  ','2011-11-22 09:33:54','2011-11-22 09:33:54'),(257,2365,4,NULL,'Q2','Always','Always','Always','Always','We have not completed a major written assessment since Kholiswa completed her formatting requirements on her persuasive piece; this is why her mark is still a 4.  She did do an excellent job presenting this piece as a speech, and has shown renewed commitment to her homework and class participation.  If these trends continue, we should expect a grade commensurate with her recent efforts.','2011-11-22 09:44:16','2011-11-22 12:09:32'),(258,2502,4,NULL,'Q2','Always','Always','Usually','Always','Zebib is starting to settle into her roles and responsibilities as an English student at ICS.  She was able to resolve the formatting issues that resulted in an INC grade during the first quarter, and has recently shown good effort on her homework assignments and has also begun to speak up in class.  I would like to see these trends continue as we move forward...If she has any questions or difficulties with any part of the course, she should be sure to speak with me.','2011-11-22 09:50:59','2011-11-22 09:50:59'),(259,2806,3,NULL,'Q2','Usually','Always','Occasionally','Usually','Cade needs more consistency in homework effort and class participation in order to achieve his academic potential, which he displayed at the end of last year.  He\'s done fine on major assessments, but needs to push himself further in terms of attention to detail and depth of analysis.  ','2011-11-22 09:58:25','2011-11-22 12:12:22'),(260,3753,7,NULL,'Q3','Occasionally','Occasionally','Unacceptable','Usually','Kurbell has not made changes to improve his work in band.  He demonstrated fantastic sound on his trombone but without practice, no improvements have been made nor heard.  Although Kurbell is polite and respectful when he speaks, he has done little in this class to even warrant a grade. For Kurbell to make changes and improve in his playing, it would only take him a few weeks of focus and practice to find the keys of playing the trombone well.  ','2012-02-14 05:29:55','2012-03-20 06:04:03'),(262,2545,5,NULL,'Q3','Usually','Usually','Usually','Usually','Christine continues to find chemistry quite challenging but shows a positive attitude. She needs to ensure that she is working on her textbook at home. If she needs clarification on this, or anything that we are doing, she needs to see me ASAP.','2012-02-14 06:47:04','2012-02-14 06:47:04'),(263,2896,5,NULL,'Q3','Usually','Always','Usually','Usually','Wuby continues to find chemistry quite challenging but shows a positive attitude. She needs to ensure that she is working on her textbook at home. If she needs clarification on this, or anything that we are doing, she needs to see me ASAP.','2012-02-14 06:52:34','2012-02-14 06:52:34'),(264,2199,5,NULL,'Q3','Occasionally','Usually','Occasionally','Usually','Prateek often seems to misunderstand what he needs to be doing and as a result doesn\'t always get his work done. If he needs clarification on anything that we are doing, he needs to see me ASAP.','2012-02-14 06:54:44','2012-02-14 06:54:44'),(265,3711,6,NULL,'Q3','Unacceptable','Occasionally','Unacceptable','Usually','Fahreen needs to decide TODAY whether she is going to aim for success of not. If she is willing to put in the work that she needs to do, I will support her every step of the way. I believe she has the potential to be successful with her IB certificate for chemistry, but it will require her to organize her time and use every resource to its fullest. Most recently,I have given Fahreen a revision folder that should help her to learn effectively, but it will only work if she uses it, putting time and effort into every part.','2012-02-14 07:48:08','2012-02-14 07:48:08'),(266,3378,6,NULL,'Q3','Occasionally','Usually','Usually','Usually','When Kaleab and I discussed his decision to take higher level chemistry last year, I don\'t think he believed how much work it would take to be successful. I think he realizes this now. Therefore, I am looking forward to supporting his efforts over the next few weeks so that he can be successful. I have recently given him a revision folder, which will help him to organize his time and actions. He needs to begin studying hard NOW and collaborating with me more to ensure efficient and effective use of his time.','2012-02-14 07:52:43','2012-02-14 08:01:46'),(267,3619,6,NULL,'Q3','Unacceptable','Occasionally','Unacceptable','Usually','Julia put in a lot of time and effort to complete her labs, and did so to a high standard. Now she needs to decide what she will do about her final exams. When Julia decided to take IB chemistry, I don\'t think she believed how much work it would take to be successful. I think she realizes this now. However, I think she has also decided to try to make it go away by ignoring it. \r\nIf Julia begins studying hard NOW and collaborating with me more to ensure efficient and effective use of her time, I truly believe she will be successful.  I have recently given her a revision folder, which will aid her to organize her time and actions, but only if she actually uses it!','2012-02-14 08:01:32','2012-02-14 08:01:32'),(268,3022,5,NULL,'Q3','Usually','Usually','Occasionally','Usually','Mikko needs to develop a routine whereby he studies chemistry \"little and often\". This course is challenging, but he will be successful if he changes his habits now. I would expect him to spend 30 minutes to an hour everyday, and he should collaborate with me on how to use his time.','2012-02-14 08:06:37','2012-02-14 08:23:35'),(269,3227,5,NULL,'Q3','Usually','Usually','Occasionally','Always','Mikeal needs to develop a routine whereby he studies chemistry \"little and often\". This course is challenging, but he will be successful if he changes his habits now. I would expect him to spend 30 minutes to an hour everyday, and he should collaborate with me on how to use his time.','2012-02-14 08:07:18','2012-02-14 08:23:19'),(270,2899,5,NULL,'Q3','Usually','Usually','Usually','Usually','Anirudh needs to develop a routine whereby he studies chemistry \"little and often\". This course is challenging, but he will be successful if he changes his habits now. I would expect him to spend 30 minutes to an hour everyday, and he should collaborate with me on how to use his time.','20