INSERT INTO `section_comments` VALUES (1,229,25,'Q3','In the first half of this semester course, we have completed two projects and begun a third. Students used the GIMP to create and edit a bitmapped image (a photograph), while learning about image file types and the advantages and disadvantages of bitmapped images. Then, they used Inkscape to create a scalable vector graphic, while comparing vector graphics with bitmapped images. We are now in the middle of a video project, shooting and editing a video using a non-linear editor. Projects are approached using a problem-solving basis: the projects must be created to meet a specific need or solve a problem.','2012-03-19 10:35:19','2012-03-23 13:08:08'),(2,185,44,'Q3','In Middle School Survey of Art, students began Quarter 3 by learning about the Elements and Principles of Art and Design.  They applied this knowledge to compositions with collaged paper and developed vocabulary they will apply all semester.  In a drawing unit, students learned technical skills to improve drawing and combined these skills with art history and creative thinking in a final drawing assignment.  At the end of the quarter, the class began a Ceramics unit, involving the study of ancient ceramic traditions. They will continue to work with clay and make connections to Art History in Quarter 4, in addition to exploring color theory through painting, linear perspective and contemporary art.  ','2012-03-19 11:10:21','2012-03-22 10:18:14'),(3,212,48,'Q3','In Middle School Physical Education during Quarter 3, instruction and learning focused on track & field and Ultimate Frisbee.  During track & field students learned the sequence of steps to execute a high jump, long jump, shot put, discuss throw, and block starts with sprints.  During Ultimate Frisbee students learned the various ways of throwing the disc along with the basic rules of the game.  Students were assessed by demonstrating various techniques and playing games.  Quarter 3 learning was focused on students correctly throwing and catching risks, using a variety of sources to reflect and improve on their performance, and to understand the tactics, choices, and options available while playing big field games.  Quarter 4 will consist of football, fieldhockey and Badminton.','2012-03-19 11:17:43','2012-03-23 14:01:29'),(4,37,43,'Q3','In 6th grade English Language Arts during Quarter 3, instruction and learning focused on reading and writing informational texts.  Students learned how to identify the six informational text structures writers use and then use their knowledge of structures to gain better understanding of the text.  One particular skill is identifying the main idea of a text.  They will also use this knowledge to help guide, inform, and organize their own writing of nonfiction.  Students were pre-assessed on report writing, and they embarked on the report writing and research process:  they chose biography subjects to report on, they located print and digital sources of information, and they evaluated sources based on their credibility.  Vocabulary, grammar, and independent reading studies continued and are ongoing components of instruction.  ','2012-03-19 11:46:06','2012-03-22 15:24:39'),(5,108,49,'Q3','','2012-03-19 12:08:23','2012-03-19 12:42:50'),(6,101,49,'Q3','This quarter 3 the Gila class has been focusing on learning some background information on global issues. Topics like sustainability, ecological footprint, and fair trade, for example, were investigated and discussed during the first weeks of our course. After that, the students, in small teams, had to focus on the issues they consider are affecting development in our host country, Ethiopia. They did research and read articles in order to produce their \"Ethiopian Issues Portrait\". Our class also had the opportunity to interview Mr. Olney, who answered the student\'s questions about what Save the Children is doing to address some of the global issues that we are studying. As part of our course, students worked on research, discussions, debates, presentations and reflections on their work. ','2012-03-19 12:09:24','2012-03-21 06:26:16'),(7,142,49,'Q3','During Quarter 3 our Spanish class has been focusing on two units: \"Comidas y Bebidas\"(Food and drinks) and \"Donde estan las llaves?\" (Where are the keys?). The students were busy learning the vocabulary related to Food and to Housing, and they worked on a number of verbs, like \"ser\", \"estar\", \"hay\", \"tener\". Emphasis was put on practicing verb conjugations and on using the correct sentence structure. We have continued working on our speaking skills through role plays and dialogs, on writing a variety of simple texts, as well as on listening and reading comprehensions. \r\nThe next steps will be to learn irregular verbs, daily routines and slowly adding more complexity to the grammatical structures used. ','2012-03-19 12:29:26','2012-03-21 06:30:47'),(8,217,44,'Q3','In Middle School Physical Education during Quarter 3, instruction and learning focused on track & field and soccer.  During track & field, students learned the sequence of steps to execute a high jump, long jump, shot put, and discuss throw.  During soccer, students learned various ways of handling the ball, dribbling, passing and shooting, along with the basic rules of the game.  Students were assessed using a video of their performance on a set short-course.  Quarter 3 learning was focused on students correctly striking and fielding balls, using a variety of sources to reflect and improve on their performance, and to understand the tactics, choices, and options available while playing small-sided games. \r\n\r\nAs we move into Quarter 4, students will continue to develop motor skills as well as psychological, social, and personal aspects of physical activity through units including field hockey and frisbee.','2012-03-19 13:09:39','2012-03-22 06:41:22'),(9,188,4,'Q3','Middle School Band was introduced with more playing 