 measuring and classifying angles, using a coordinate grid to plot points, translate, flip and rotate images, as well as using properties  of  angles, triangles, parallelograms, and transversals.  Problem solving strategies will be emphasized as students will be challenged to apply all their learning to solve open-ended word problem type questions. ','2012-03-22 07:27:16','2012-03-22 07:27:16'),(24,41,34,'Q3','In quarter 3 students began to study theme in depth, identifying the theme of poems and books and supporting their ideas with evidence from the text.  Students also worked on a book response project that allowed them to showcase many skills, such as comparison, summary, and theme, in the format of their choice.  We are currently in the middle of a historical fiction novel study.  The novel takes place in Medieval Europe, the same time period being studied in social studies class.  Students are analyzing the novel using discussions in groups and various note taking strategies and written responses.  In quarter 4 we will continue the novel study as a way to continue to develop the skills learned throughout the year.  We will also use the novel as a mentor text to help students write their own historical fiction short story.  We will end the year studying argumentative writing, reading and analyzing the point of view of authors as well as writing an argument essay.','2012-03-22 07:27:32','2012-03-22 07:27:32'),(25,40,34,'Q3','In quarter 3 students began to study theme in depth, identifying the theme of poems and books and supporting their ideas with evidence from the text.  Students also worked on a book response project that allowed them to showcase many skills, such as comparison, summary, and theme, in the format of their choice.  We are currently in the middle of a historical fiction novel study.  The novel takes place in Medieval Europe, the same time period being studied in social studies class.  Students are analyzing the novel using discussions in groups 